The paper deals with the problem of distributed function computation, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the structure of functions to be computed, which is a topic in discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science (cs.DS). The paper proposes a new method for deriving a converse bound for distributed computing, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also characterizes the optimal rate for computing certain types of functions, which is a topic in signal processing and information theory (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the optimal rate for computing functions that are compositions of symbol-wise functions and the type of a sequence, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC).
